data.title: University of Missouri-St. Louis Digital Library
data.text:
Title

West's Painting of Death on the Pale Horse

Description

Handbook describing the exhibition of the painting, 'Death on the Pale Horse' by Benjamin West at the Hall of the St. Louis Fire Company

Title

President Exterior

Description

Photograph, taken in the evening, of the bow of the President steamboat. The Gateway Arch is visible in the background., p11-3-3-57-4

Title

Arcturus and Robert E. Lee

Description

French Boat "Arcturus". 7/2/76. "Str. Robert E. Lee" on right

Title

Jefferson Barracks, St. Louis, Missouri

Description

A view of the lawn and a collection of red brick buildings at Jefferson Barracks, south of St. Louis in Missouri, Built in 1826, Jefferson Barracks is the oldest military installation west of the the Mississippi River.

Title

Admiral Ballroom

Description

Photograph of a children's dance recital in the Admiral steamboat. Passengers of the steamboat observe the scene from the ballroom floor and the balcony.

Title

University Club

Description

Photograph of the University Club building in St. Louis.

Title

Franklin Avenue Restaurant

Description

Restaurant and caf√© on Franklin Avenue.

Title

Control Tower

Description

Photograph from inside the control tower south of Union Station. A worker looks out over the railway lines as a train passes.

Title

Admiral Construction

Description

Photograph of the construction of the superstructure of the Admiral with men in the foreground., P11-3-1-40-8

Title

Lambert Airfield

Description

Military plane flies over Lambert Airfield.

Title

Substandard Dwelling Unites

Description

Plate number seven. Obsolete dwellings breed slums. Slums are the direct outgrowth of obsolete substandard housing., From: Report / City Plan Commission of St. Louis. [St. Louis] : City Plan Commission of St. Louis. 1942.

Title

Wine of Cardui

Description

Photograph of drugstore window advertising "Wine of Cardui", a patent medicine in the late Nineteenth and early Twentieth centuries.

Title

Leo Durocher and Buckey Harris

Description

Leo Durocher and Buckey (sic) Harris (right), managers of the rival clubs, were all smiles before the game got under way. Harris pulled the surprise package out of the game in Vic Raschi who not only pitched two hitless innings but drove across two vital runs.

Title

St. Louis Zoo Lion Show

Description

Photograph of lions lifting their training into the air by pulling a rope beneath him during a lion show at the St. Louis Zoo. A crowd looks down at the scene from above.

Title

These 14 Cars Sold To The City Of St. Louis

Description

Photograph of fleet of Ford Model T automobiles in front of St. Louis city hall. Drivers are in each car, several men are standing in front of the cars holding a banner that reads "These 14 cars sold to the city of St. Louis, watch the Fords go by."

Title

Lindell Hotel

Description

Photograph of the Lindell Hotel at Eighth and Washington in 1867 bore it burned down that same year.

Title

Clyde Bill of Lading

Description

Bill of lading for the Steamer CLYDE for shipment of 27 tons #1 pig iron and 15 tons #2 pig iron, May 14, 1886 to St. Louis, Missouri, for the La Grange Iron Co. at $2.00 per ton.

Title

Arcturus

Description

French Navy patrol craft "Arcturus" 154 ft. diesel-powered boat. Crew of 35.

Title

Admiral Boarding/Disembarking

Description

Photograph of passengers disembarking the gangplank of the Admiral with the Eads Bridge in the background., p11-3-1-40-5
